<subSubSection id="62171D2CA4E56586B784715A618E55C7" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="C2230692E6240D803850966435043D58" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="6D36343CB062BB519A27D006B82774FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
The specific name 
<taxonomicName id="3FDA5DEB46C9AA0A5F5D3A4088B88E78" authorityName="Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Hirudinida" family="Hirudinidae" genus="Hirudo" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hirudo tianjinensis" order="Arhynchobdellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tianjinensis">
<emphasis id="945E036D3CCF0C836D03854CACBBEB0F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Hirudo tianjinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is derived from Tianjin City, a municipality directly under the central government in China, where type specimens were collected.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="AE4413B6E01C2302F1C2CAD159869AED" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="551DE02C9BCA3170CA661D28080314A7" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="10CC756141D7106FB7F28EDB5155C64D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName id="C36CB0684E100E4866FC74C2EB8C4E99" authorityName="Liu" authorityYear="2022" class="Hirudinida" family="Hirudinidae" genus="Hirudo" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hirudo tianjinensis" order="Arhynchobdellida" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Annelida" rank="species" species="tianjinensis">
<emphasis id="00F992D71CAF0ECE8A06A5B2A41D2F40" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Hirudo tianjinensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected from Caobai River, Haogezhuang Town, Baodi District, Tianjin City, China, which flows into Bohai Sea. Water was moderately polluted. Aquatic plants and irregular pumice stones were abundant along the riverbed. This species normally hid under pumice stones. Whenever people and animals pass by, it quickly adsorbs on their ankles for sucking blood.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
